DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,4,1);
$b = random(3,6,1);
$c = random(10,20,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Suppose that \(x = x(t)\) and \(y=y(t)\) are both functions of
\(t\).  If
\[
    y = $a x^2 - 1,
\]
and \(\frac{dx}{dt} = $b\) when \(x = $c\), what is \(\frac{dy}{dt}\)?
$BR
$BR
\(\frac{dy}{dt}\) = \{ans_rule(20) \}
$BR

EOT

$ans = 2*$a*$c*$b;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION') );
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR
\(\frac{dy}{dt}=2($a)x\frac{dx}{dt}\)
$BR \(=2($a)($c)$b\)
$BR \(=$ans\)
END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
